d%20yet%20with%20a%20certain%20relief%2C%20the%20protagonist%2C%20Eilish%2C%20finds%20herself%20by%20the%20window%20watching%20outside.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cdarkening%20garden%E2%80%9D%20outside%20becomes%20a%20dreadful%20sight%2C%20because%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20of%20that%20darkness%20has%20come%20into%20the%20house.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProphet%20Song%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20then%20is%2C%20from%20this%20first%20scene%2C%20a%20novel%20that%20allows%20darkness%20a%20corporeal%20form%20%E2%80%93%20something%20that%20breaches%20thresholds%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efollows%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHome%20and%20the%20World%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20darkness%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efollows%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20not%20only%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20universe.%20As%20the%20story%20unfolds%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20this%20is%20also%20the%20darkness%20of%20our%20own%20world%20and%20time.%20Children%E2%80%99s%20hospitals%20being%20bombed%2C%20houses%20of%20minorities%20being%20demolished%2C%20detainment%20of%20political%20dissenters%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20these%20events%20are%20too%20familiar%20to%20us%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20hardly%20anything%20%E2%80%9Cdystopian%E2%80%9D%20about%20Lynch%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20universe%2C%20even%20though%20it%20has%20been%20called%20so.%20Perhaps%20it%20is%20our%20collective%20ignorance%20%E2%80%93%20the%20unsettling%20novel%20suggests%20%E2%80%93%20that%20allows%20us%20to%20think%20that%20genocide%20is%20a%20local%20or%20regional%20issue.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProphet%20Song%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20violently%20shakes%20us%20out%20of%20that%20illusion%2C%20and%20simultaneously%20redeems%20one%E2%80%99s%20faith%20in%20the%20incredible%20power%20of%20art%20to%20reveal%20the%20festering%20rot%20of%20the%20society.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20Lynch%E2%80%99s%20novel%20is%20a%20breathless%20passage%20about%20how%20the%20%E2%80%9Cend%20of%20the%20world%20is%20always%20a%20local%20event.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20the%20prophet%20sings%20not%20of%20the%20end%20of%20the%20world%20but%20of%20what%20has%20been%20done%20and%20what%20will%20be%20done%20and%20what%20is%20being%20done%20to%20some%20but%20not%20others%2C%20that%20the%20world%20is%20always%20ending%20over%20and%20over%20again%20in%20one%20place%20but%20not%20another%20and%20that%20the%20end%20of%20the%20world%20is%20always%20a%20local%20event%2C%20it%20comes%20to%20your%20country%20and%20visits%20your%20town%20and%20knocks%20on%20the%20door%20of%20your%20house%20and%20becomes%20to%20others%20but%20some%20distant%20warning%2C%20a%20brief%20report%20on%20the%20news%2C%20an%20echo%20of%20events%20that%20has%20passed%20into%20folklore%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20this%20presumably%20perfect%20binary%20between%20the%20Self%20and%20the%20Other%20and%2For%20the%20Home%20and%20the%20World%20that%20the%20novel%20breaches.%20The%20personal%20and%20the%20political%20collide%20in%20the%20most%20scintillating%20manner%20in%20the%20novel%2C%20as%20the%20violence%20of%20totalitarianism%20wreaks%20havoc%20on%20an%20unsuspecting%20family.%20And%20this%20is%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20to%20reveal%20to%20the%20readers%20their%20own%20ignorance%20and%20privilege.%20All%20%E2%80%9Clocal%E2%80%9D%20ends%20of%20the%20world%2C%20it%20asserts%2C%20are%20really%20universal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20world%E2%80%99s%20derision%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20daunting%20challenges%20of%20art%20is%20to%20be%20seen%20for%20what%20it%20is.%20Between%20interpellations%20and%20interpretations%2C%20the%20meanings%20that%20we%20ascribe%20to%20artworks%20become%20more%20convoluted%20than%20they%20are%20intended%20to%20be%20%E2%80%93%20or%20otherwise.%20Which%20is%20also%20to%20say%20that%20art%20is%20also%20easily%20informed%20by%20the%20persisting%20%E2%80%9Cregime%20of%20truth%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20Michel%20Foucault%20suggested.%20But%20Lynch%20confronts%20the%20problem%20by%20telling%20the%20story%20as%20it%20is.%20There%20is%20a%20desolation%20in%20the%20prose%3A%20The%20sentences%20are%20often%20structured%20in%20a%20way%20where%20the%20action%20precedes%20the%20subject%3B%20almost%20as%20if%20you%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Elooking%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eat%20the%20event%2C%20not%20reading%20about%20it.%20The%20novel%20forces%20you%20to%20witness%20the%20illogic%20violence%20and%20banality%20of%20totalitarianism.%20The%20language%20itself%20is%20ingeniously%20broken%20%E2%80%93%20although%20never%20ungrammatical%20%E2%80%93%20and%20schizophrenic.%20After%20all%2C%20how%20can%20language%20sustain%20its%20structures%20and%20semantics%20in%20a%20broken%20world%3F%20When%20the%20centre%20does%20not%20hold%2C%20all%20comes%20crashing%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20uncanny%20and%20compounded%20writing%2C%20the%20novel%20also%20perfectly%20engenders%20the%20mindspace%20of%20its%20protagonist.%20Eilish%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20four%20children%20%E2%80%93%20including%20an%20infant%20%E2%80%93%20is%20suddenly%20thrown%20into%20an%20unknown%2C%20desolate%20world%20when%20her%20husband%20mysteriously%20vanishes%20one%20day.%20Her%20previously%20ordinary%20life%20is%20vehemently%20replaced%20by%20the%20everydayness%20of%20loss%2C%20fear%2C%20paranoia%20and%20numbness.%20Eilish%20represents%20the%20unseen%20victims%20of%20political%20vendetta%20and%20intimidation%20%E2%80%93%20the%20families%20of%20those%20incarcerated%20under%20absurd%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fuapa-case-data-process-punishment-home-ministry-rajya-sabha%5C%22%3Edraconian%20laws%20like%20UAPA%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20most%20hard-hitting%20scenes%20in%20the%20novel%20are%20when%20Eilish%20is%20in%20a%20sort%20of%20trance%2C%20in%20which%20she%20cannot%20think%20or%20access%20her%20own%20body%20and%20emotions.%20She%20seems%20to%20be%20looking%20at%20herself%20from%20the%20outside.%20Her%20relationship%20with%20her%20body%20changes%2C%20wherein%20she%20is%20only%20a%20shell%2C%20an%20emptiness%2C%20and%20her%20life%20seems%20to%20be%20happening%20at%20some%20unfathomable%20distance.%20This%20is%20achieved%20so%20masterfully%20in%20Lynch%E2%80%99s%20language%2C%20which%20is%20always%20dissociated%E2%80%A6%20almost%20in%20a%20state%20of%20shock%20about%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20situations%20in%20this%20totalitarian%20regime%2C%20but%20witnessing%20it%20regardless%20with%20an%20urgent%20disconnection%20of%20the%20mind.%20Esi%20Edugyan%2C%20Chair%20of%20the%202023%20Booker%20judges%2C%20has%20lauded%20the%20book%20for%20its%20atmosphere%20of%20%E2%80%9Csustained%20claustrophobia%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20it%20is%20through%20truly%20astounding%20gymnastics%20of%20language%20that%20Lynch%20performs%20%E2%80%93%20pushing%20language%20to%20its%20limits%20%E2%80%93%20to%20achieve%20that%20effect.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20prophets%E2%80%99%20songs%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20may%20not%20be%20incorrect%20to%20suggest%20that%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20cataclysmic%20global%20events%2C%20apathy%20has%20become%20a%20staple%20response%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunaffected.%E2%80%9D%20We%20seem%20to%20have%20more%20moral%20compunctions%20about%20the%20way%20an%20oppressed%20group%20responds%20to%20state-sanctioned%20violence%20than%20the%20state-sanctioned%20violence%20itself.%20In%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20I%20have%20heard%20people%20talk%20about%20%E2%80%9Cnuanced%20history%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cunverifiable%20facts.%E2%80%9D%20Also%20that%20the%20conflict%20is%20so%20distant%20for%20them%20(geographically%20and%20politically)%20that%20they%20find%20it%20irrelevant%20to%20have%20an%20opinion%20about%20it.%20Millions%20of%20refugees%20and%20more%20than%2018%2C000%20murdered%20(as%20of%20early%20December)%20do%20not%20affect%20us%20between%20our%20nine-to-fives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20overexposed%20hyperreality%20we%20live%20in%20has%20somehow%20convinced%20us%20that%20life%20is%20too%20short%20to%20be%20so%20angry%20about%20everything.%20That%20apathy%20should%20be%20normalised%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20better%20than%20%E2%80%9Carmchair%20activism.%E2%80%9D%20Recently%20someone%20on%20the%20Internet%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9CFree%20Palestine%E2%80%9D%20placards%20at%20Delhi%20Pride%20parade%20were%20redundant.%20The%20participants%20were%20told%20to%20pick%20their%20battles.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProphet%20Song%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reminds%20us%20that%20this%20choice%20is%20not%20real.%20In%20its%20unblinking%20courage%2C%20this%20is%20a%20book%20that%20asks%20to%20be%20looked%20in%20the%20eyes.%20How%20do%20we%20decide%20when%20the%20personal%20becomes%20political%20%E2%80%93%20and%20vice%20versa%3F%20There%20is%20truly%20no%20distinction%2C%20Lynch%20suggests.%20And%20I%20think%20this%20is%20the%20function%20of%20literature%20and%20art%3A%20To%20slap%20us%20in%20the%20face%20and%20wake%20us%20up%20from%20our%20apathy%20and%20complicity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20year%2C%20as%20a%20writer%20wins%20the%20Booker%20or%20a%20Nobel%20Prize%2C%20we%20rush%20to%20read%20their%20books%2C%20find%20out%20how%20they%20perceive%20the%20world.%20Suddenly%20we%20are%20thrown%20into%20an%20Irish%20wasteland%2C%20a%20Norwegian%20desolation%2C%20a%20Sri%20Lankan%20battlefield.%20A%20short-lived%2C%20trend-spotting%20curiosity.%20To%20tell%20the%20truth%20as%20it%20is%2C%20is%20an%20increasingly%20rare%20feat%20in%20our%20world%2C%20where%20eminent%20international%20dailies%20have%20resorted%20to%20coining%20phrases%20like%20%E2%80%9Cfragile%20lives%20found%20ended%E2%80%9D%20to%20refer%20to%20the%20children%20being%20murdered%20in%20a%20harrowing%20genocide.%20One%20hopes%20the%20jarring%20warnings%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProphet%20Song%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20live%20on%2C%20and%20resound%20and%20haunt%20us%20with%20their%20music.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKartik%20Chauhan%20works%20in%20publishing%20and%20writes%20about%20stories%20that%20pry%20open%20the%20world%20around%20him.%20He%20is%20on%20X%20%40karteakk%20and%20on%20Instagram%2C%C2%A0%40karkritiques.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702719920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090716%2FUntitled-design-6-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fpaul-lynch-prophet-song-personal-political%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22How%20do%20we%20decide%20when%20the%20personal%20becomes%20political%20%E2%80%93%20and%20vice%20versa%3F%20There%20is%20truly%20no%20distinction%2C%20Lynch%20suggests.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fpaul-lynch-prophet-song-personal-political%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20best%20advice%20for%20female%20entrepreneurs%20from%20the%20founders%20of%20SoulCycle%2C%20Poppi%2C%20Halfdays%2C%20and%20more%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223219%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Julie%20Rice%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20SoulCycle%2C%20is%20pictured%20sitting%20onstage%20holding%20a%20microphone%20and%20talking%20to%20Female%20Founder%20World%20creator%20Jasmine%20Garnsworthy%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20a%20pink%20Female%20Founder%20World%20summit%20logo.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%