ck.com%2Fredirect%2Fe8fe6211-c296-4726-809b-29273b1c3100%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702787726126000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0610QZ-w8cmgWWKCHFmvvM%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobalisation%20paradox%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fiercely%20argued%20at%20a%20time%20when%20supply-side%2C%20neoliberal%20economic%20ideology%20and%20a%20hyper-globalisation%20wave%20%E2%80%93%20built%20around%20a%20need%20to%20unconditionally%20enable%20cross-border%20capital%20movements%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20domestic%20macroeconomic%20stabilisation%2C%20particularly%20in%20developing%20economies%20%E2%80%93%20ruled%20the%20roost.%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20work%20made%20space%20for%20mainstream%20critical%20voices%20among%20economists%20and%20in%20policy%20about%20the%20limitations%20of%20hyper-globalism%20advocated%20within%20the%20neoliberalism%20paradigm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20Medellin%2C%20Rodrik%20offered%20a%20new%20approach%20as%20a%20theory%20of%20economic%20change%20built%20around%20%E2%80%98good%20jobs%E2%80%99%2C%20drawing%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fb3ccf565-fd92-4e79-961f-980d0235525c%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fb3ccf565-fd92-4e79-961f-980d0235525c%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702787726126000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw19_A8SIGNNwR2c6fij9yKG%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20recent%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20postulates%20a%20new%20theoretical%20approach%20for%20countries%20struggling%20to%20rebalance%20policy%20priorities%20aimed%20at%20a%20need%20to%20globalise%20(via%20trade%2C%20finance%2C%20flexible%20immigration%20laws)%20and%20also%20secure%20a%20domestic-focused%20commitment%20to%20socio-cultural%20%E2%80%98national%20priorities%E2%80%99%20(often%20wrapped%20in%20an%20ideological%2C%20majoritarian%20agenda).%20Much%20of%20the%20populist%20imagination%20of%20the%20political%20Right%20concerns%20the%20need%20to%20meet%20these%20two%20goals%2C%20and%20they%20have%20constantly%20struggled%20due%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20alternative%20theory%20of%20economic%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERodrik%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fb3ccf565-fd92-4e79-961f-980d0235525c%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fb3ccf565-fd92-4e79-961f-980d0235525c%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702787726126000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw19_A8SIGNNwR2c6fij9yKG%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalls%20this%20new%20approach%20(to%20the%20theory%20of%20economic%20change)%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98productivism%E2%80%99.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fb3ccf565-fd92-4e79-961f-980d0235525c%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2Fb3ccf565-fd92-4e79-961f-980d0235525c%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702787726126000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw19_A8SIGNNwR2c6fij9yKG%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20him%2C%20it%20can%20help%20%E2%80%9Cprioritise%20the%20dissemination%20of%20productive%20economic%20opportunities%20throughout%20all%20regions%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20segments%20of%20the%20labour%20force.%E2%80%9D%20It%20differs%20from%20neoliberalism%20in%20giving%20governments%20and%20civil%20society%20a%20significant%20role.%20It%20puts%20less%20faith%20in%20markets%20and%20is%20suspicious%20of%20large%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProductivism%2C%20as%20a%20normative%20and%20applied%20policy%20approach%2C%20emphasises%20%E2%80%9Cproduction%20and%20investment%20over%20finance%2C%20and%20revitalising%20local%20communities%20over%20globalisation.%20It%20also%20departs%20from%20the%20Keynesian%20welfare%20state%20%E2%80%93%20the%20paradigm%20that%20neoliberalism%20replaced%20%E2%80%95%20by%20focusing%20less%20on%20redistribution%2C%20social%20transfers%20and%20macroeconomic%20management%20and%20more%20on%20creating%20economic%20opportunity%20by%20working%20on%20the%20supply%20side%20of%20the%20economy%20to%20create%20good%2C%20productive%20jobs%20for%20everyone%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20the%20paradigm%20%E2%80%9Cdiverges%20from%20both%20of%20its%20antecedents%20by%20exhibiting%20greater%20scepticism%20towards%20technocrats%20and%20being%20less%20instinctively%20hostile%20to%20populism%20in%20the%20economic%20sphere%E2%80%9D%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20its%20nomenclature%20aside%20from%20a%20political%20economy%20perspective%2C%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20approach%20combines%20key%20policy%20ingredients%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESafeguard%20%E2%80%98good%20jobs%E2%80%99%20to%20help%20the%20upward%20mobility%20of%20the%20lower%20socio-economic%20class%2C%20which%20failed%20to%20get%20much%20from%20neoliberalism%2C%20and%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETake%20the%20%E2%80%98productivity%E2%80%99%20debate%20in%20economic%20policy%20back%20to%20a%20labour-intensive%20sectoral%20focus%2C%20which%20is%20critical%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20middle-income%20groups%20from%20the%20upward%20mobility%20of%20the%20poor.%20This%20remained%20central%20to%20the%20developmental%20stories%20(and%20socio-economic%20mobility)%20of%20post-80s%20China%20and%20post-90s%20India.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20focus%20on%20labour-intensive%20productivity%2C%20not%20just%20in%20manufacturing%20but%20also%20in%20low-skill%20services%20(for%20India)%2C%20that%20enables%20good%20employment%2C%20rebuilds%20domestic%20supply%20chains%2C%20ensures%20better%20working%20conditions%20(especially%20for%20women)%2C%20and%20provides%20a%20better%20redistributive%20environment%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20fiscal%20choices%2C%20can%20offer%20a%20useful%20ideological%20approach%20to%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20which%20are%20anchored%20without%20any%20theory%20of%20economic%20change%20by%20the%20current%20government.%20The%20issues%20are%20not%20restricted%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%20after%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20we%20saw%20this%20in%20the%20way%20the%20Joe%20Biden%20administration%20pivoted%20its%20economic%20policy.%20According%20to%20Rodrik%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20wholesale%20embrace%20of%20industrial%20policies%20to%20facilitate%20the%20green%20transition%2C%20rebuild%20domestic%20supply%20chains%20and%20stimulate%20good%20jobs%2C%20the%20finger-pointing%20at%20corporate%20profits%20as%20a%20partial%20culprit%20behind%20inflation%2C%20and%20the%20refusal%20(so%20far)%20to%20revoke%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20tariffs%20against%20China%20are%20some%20examples.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Vanishing%20Middle%20Class%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017)%2C%20MIT%20economic%20historian%20Peter%20Temin%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Lewis%20model%20of%20a%20dual%20economy%20had%20become%20increasingly%20relevant%20to%20the%20US.%20According%20to%20Temin%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20forces%20%E2%80%93%20de-industrialisation%2C%20globalisation%2C%20new%20technologies%20that%20favour%20professionals%20and%20capitalists%2C%20and%20declining%20protections%20for%20labour%20%E2%80%93%20have%20produced%20a%20widening%20gap%20between%20winners%20and%20those%20left%20behind.%20Convergence%20between%20poor%20and%20rich%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%20was%20arrested%2C%20labour%20markets%20became%20increasingly%20polarised%20between%20highly%20educated%20workers%20and%20the%20rest%2C%20and%20regional%20disparities%20widened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20look%20at%20output-employment%20growth%20in%20the%20last%20six%20years%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20from%20the%20post-demonetisation%20period%20(2016)%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%20fall%20in%20overall%20output%20(if%20we%20only%20look%20at%20industrial%20production%20levels)%20and%20in%20the%20aggregate%20employment%20rate%20of%20the%20eligible%20job-seeking%20population.%20Even%20more%20strikingly%2C%20the%20female%20employment%20rate%20has%20dropped%20from%2011.88%25%20(2016-17)%20to%207.96%25%20(2021-22).%20In%20urban%20areas%2C%20for%20women%2C%20it%20has%20dropped%20from%2010.77%25%20to%205.57%25%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202016-2021%2C%20the%20top%2020%25%20rich%20have%20seen%20almost%20a%2040%25%20rise%20in%20income%20growth%20while%20the%20middle%2020%25%2C%20lower%20middle%2020%25%20and%20poorest%2020%25%20have%20all%20seen%20negative%20income%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Temin%20phenomenon%20is%20visible%20in%20a%20vanishing%20middle%20class%2C%20which%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20received%20a%20better%20bargain%20from%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20economic%20policies%2C%20and%20has%20lost%20more%20than%20it%20gained%20in%20terms%20of%20jobs%20and%20income%20growth.%20Rising%20inflation%20in%20the%20essentials%20basket%20adversely%20impacts%20real%20wages%2C%20consumption%20and%20demand-supply%20issues%2C%20making%20the%20poor%20worse%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProductivism%20can%20bring%20economic%20policy%20change%20back%20to%20key%20focal%20points.%20An%20elected%20government%20needs%20to%20be%20the%20guide%20of%20change%20in%20economic%20policy%2C%20and%20Opposition%20politics%20in%20India%20would%20need%20to%20have%20a%20good%20sense%20of%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%2C%20and%20how.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20policy%20paradigms%2C%20from%20mercantilism%20to%20Keynesianism%20and%20neoliberalism%2C%20were%20primarily%20economists%E2%80%99%20paradigms%20and%20according%20to%20Rodrik%2C%20had%20significant%20blind%20spots%20when%20it%20came%20to%20key%20social%2C%20cultural%20and%20national%20priority%20issues%20(which%20is%20what%20gave%20rise%20to%20an%20alternative%20imagination%20of%20the%20political%20and%20economic%20establishment%20dominated%20by%20right-wing%20strongman%20politics).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Rodrik%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20societies%20are%20confronted%20today%20with%20vital%20challenges%20that%20require%20new%20economic%20approaches%20and%20significant%20policy%20experimentation.%20But%20those%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20economic%20paradigm%20%E2%80%93%20or%20actively%20trying%20to%20develop%20one%20%E2%80%95%20should%20be%20careful%20what%20they%20are%20wishing%20for.%20By%20the%20time%20a%20set%20of%20ideas%20become%20conventional%20wisdom%2C%20it%20is%20riddled%20with%20one-size-fits-all%20generalisations.%20Our%20goal%20should%20be%20not%20to%20create%20tomorrow%E2%80%99s%20ossified%20vision%2C%20but%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20adapt%20our%20policies%20and%20institutions%20to%20changing%20exigencies.%20Productivism%20may%20be%20the%20right%20approach%20for%20today%E2%80%99s%20challenges.%20Yet%20the%20more%20successful%20it%20is%2C%20the%20less%20relevant%20it%20will%20become%20to%20future%20challenges.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20politics%20in%20India%20would%20need%20to%20adopt%20a%20new%20economic%20theory%20of%20change%2C%20built%20upon%20the%20progressive%20ideas%20(and%20policy%20approaches)%20of%20productivism%2C%20focusing%20on%20issues%20vital%20to%20a%20vanishing%20middle%20class%2C%20while%20creating%20an%20aspirational%20trajectory%20of%20upward%20mobility%20for%20the%20(low-middle)%20income%20groups%20left%20behind%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20jobs%2C%20output%20production%20processes%2C%20tech%20skills%20integration%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20OP%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702702759000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F21125255%2F8390776653_73b3382876_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fvanishing-middle-class-struggling-opposition-productivism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Productivism%20differs%20from%20neoliberalism%20in%20giving%20governments%20and%20civil%20society%20a%20significant%20role.%20It%20puts%20less%20faith%20in%20markets%20and%20is%20suspicious%20of%20large%20corporations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fvanishing-middle-class-struggling-opposition-productivism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20defends%20bounties%20offered%20for%20Hong%20Kong%20dissidents%20abroad%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702702405000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106038831%2Cimgsize-1221003.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-defends-bounties-offered-f