Charu%20enters%20the%20sport%20of%20squash%2C%20played%20by%20Gopi%2C%20who%20narrates%20the%20book.%20Gopi%20develops%20a%20romantic%20friendship%20with%20Ged.%20Ged%E2%80%99s%20mother%20runs%20the%20bar%20above%20the%20squash%20court%2C%20Western%20Lane.%20Uncle%20Pavan%20is%20a%20calm%20and%20tortured%20person.%20Aunt%20Ranjan%20is%20severe%20but%20also%20quiet%20and%20conservative.%20Maqsud%20is%20Pakistani%20and%20clearly%20the%20local%20squash%20advisor%E2%80%A6%20The%20book%20has%20very%20few%20characters%20and%20most%20dance%20around%20the%20sport%2C%20doing%20very%20little%20and%20mostly%20observing%20things%20in%20their%20own%20time.%20Men%2C%20women%2C%20boys%20and%20girls%20are%20remembered%20with%20sighs%2C%20minuscule%20gestures%20and%20the%20shortest%20of%20sentences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20result%20is%20startling%20and%20sweeping.%20It%20pushes%20the%20reader%20into%20herself%2C%20pulls%20a%20blanket%20over%20her%20and%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20mere%20160%20pages%2C%20almost%20chastens%20her.%20You%20emerge%20from%20the%20book%20thinking%20that%20everything%20that%20is%20not%20the%20bare%20and%20unspoken%20truth%20is%20immaterial%20to%20life%20and%20existence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhich%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20the%20book%20has%20no%20frivolity%20or%20fun.%20Mona%2C%20Kush%20and%20Gopi%20are%20young%20girls%2C%20after%20all.%20But%20the%20book%20does%20them%20a%20giant%20service%20the%20way%20women%20writers%20writing%20girls%20can%20and%20often%20have.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20it%20not%20only%20takes%20Gopi%E2%80%99s%20fierce%20understanding%20of%20squash%20seriously%2C%20it%20offers%20significant%20space%20to%20her%20to%20allow%20her%20to%20express%20her%20personal%20philosophy%20of%20the%20sport.%20What%20does%20it%20feel%20like%20to%20be%20alone%20in%20the%20T%20of%20the%20court%3F%20How%20do%20players%20think%20of%20throwaway%20advice%20on%20their%20game%3F%20There%20is%20a%20holiness%20associated%20with%20hearing%20sportspersons%20talk%20of%20their%20internal%20compulsions%20while%20playing%20%E2%80%93%20Maroo%20accords%20it%20all%20to%20her%20young%20protagonist.%20She%20raises%20her%20love%20for%20squash%20to%20a%20holy%20plane%2C%20positing%20as%20her%20inspiration%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20in%20the%20sport%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DBc7BoBFpdvw%5C%22%3Ereal-life%20Pakistani%20hero%20Jahangir%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20one%20allows%20young%20girls%20to%20speak%20this%20way%20%E2%80%93%20to%20have%20a%20sacred%20sense%20of%20seriousness%20over%20a%20world%20like%20sports%20which%20is%20quite%20abundantly%20occupied%20by%20men.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20respects%20the%20unshorn%20grit%20that%20girls%20have%2C%20and%20also%20that%20essential%20teenage%20experience%20%E2%80%93%20of%20that%20gigantic%20internal%20churn%20when%20society%2C%20family%20and%20you%20yourself%20are%20pulling%20yourself%20in%20different%20directions.%20Here%20too%2C%20brevity%20is%20beautiful.%20With%20the%20overarching%20tool%20of%20grief%2C%20Maroo%20delves%20into%20that%20liminal%20state%20and%20offers%20the%20reader%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20revelation.%20Her%20technique%20is%20so%20sharp%20that%20it%20strikes%20you%20as%20otherworldly%20in%20a%20world%20of%20novels%20dealing%20in%20fantasy%20or%20sharp%20realism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20a%20work%20of%20words%2C%20this%20story%20of%20an%20immigrant%20Gujarati%20Jain%20family%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20silences.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMaroo%E2%80%99s%20readers%20are%20sure%20to%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20shattering%20quiet%20that%20occupies%20houses%20after%20deaths.%20But%20they%20may%20not%20be%20aware%20of%20how%20a%20novel%20can%20feast%20on%20this%20silence.%20The%20wordlessness%20is%20tyranny%20to%20the%20reader%20but%20to%20the%20inhabitants%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20and%20calm%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20almost%20stark%20in%20its%20beauty.%20Feelings%20pass%20from%20Gopi%20to%20Pa%2C%20from%20Kush%20to%20Pa%2C%20from%20Pa%20to%20Ged%E2%80%99s%20mom%2C%20from%20Gopi%20to%20Ged%2C%20from%20character%20to%20character%2C%20like%20notes%20are%20carried%20by%20instruments%20in%20a%20concerto.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20this%20passage%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20where%20Pa%20is%20tired%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20Gopi%20who%20speaks%20of%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98You%20can%20stop%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20placed%20the%20racket%20gently%20on%20the%20floor.%20He%20looked%20so%20tired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99m%20tired%2C%E2%80%99%20I%20said.%20My%20heart%20was%20beating%20hard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98I%20know.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20can%20a%20work%20of%20art%20be%20so%20devoid%20of%20artifice%3F%20The%20reader%20is%20forced%20to%20wonder.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWestern%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ELane%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20triumph%20of%20the%20form%20of%20the%20novel%20while%20at%20once%20challenging%20the%20role%20it%20can%20play%20in%20representing%20realities%20otherwise%20familiar%20to%20its%20trope.%20That%20it%20is%20Maroo%E2%80%99s%20debut%20novel%20is%20a%20startling%20fact.%20Nowhere%20does%20the%20sanctity%20of%20her%20unique%20tone%20falter%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20in%20the%20novel%20that%20is%20not%20deeply%20sacred%20to%20loss.%20And%20squash.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702690225000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16050308%2FIMG_6733.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fchetna-maroo-western-lane-booker-squash-no