%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F03152630%2FFqMbzwUWAAAmT01.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Delays%20in%20the%20indigenous%20licensed%20manufacture%20of%20Russian%20Kalashnikov%20AK-203%20assault%20rifles%20at%20a%20dedicated%20facility%20in%20Korwa%20near%20Amethi%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20has%20further%20raised%20concerns%20in%20domestic%20military%20circles%20over%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20deliver%20assorted%20contracted-for%20platforms%20and%20other%20materiel%20to%20India%20on%20time%2C%20or%20if%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20sanguinity%20expressed%20periodically%20by%20Russian%20officials%20and%20diplomats%20to%20their%20Indian%20counterparts%20%E2%80%93%20over%20the%20fact%20that%20their%20military-industrial%20complex%20remained%20robust%20and%20was%20%E2%80%98on%20stream%E2%80%99%20to%20vindicate%20its%20equipment%20delivery%20schedules%2C%20US-led%20sanctions%20on%20Moscow%20for%20invading%20Ukraine%20have%2C%20in%20reality%20severely%20jeopardised%20its%20capacities%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20deficit%20surfaced%20visibly%20in%20the%20inability%20of%20the%20Indo-Russian%20Rifles%20Private%20Limited%20(IRRPL)%20joint%20venture%20(JV)%2C%20instituted%20in%20late%202021%2C%20to%20deliver%20the%20first%20batch%20of%20around%205%2C000%20AK-203%207.62x39mm%20rifles%20to%20the%20Indian%20Army%2C%20by%20March%202024.%20Instead%2C%20at%20the%20Indian%20Army%E2%80%99s%20prompting%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20recently%20approved%20the%20add-on%20import%20of%20around%2073%2C000%20%E2%80%98Patrol%E2%80%99%20Sig%20Sauer%20assault%20rifles%20from%20the%20US%2C%20for%20an%20estimated%20Rs%20840%20crores%2C%20to%20meet%20the%20forces%E2%80%99%20urgent%20operational%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20official%20statement%20on%20this%20postponement%20in%20supplying%20the%20AK-203s%20to%20the%20Indian%20Army%20units%20has%20been%20forthcoming%2C%20from%20either%20IRRPL%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20or%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence.%20But%20industry%20sources%20said%20that%20the%20economic%20and%20technological%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%2C%20were%20together%20responsible%20for%20deferrals%20in%20even%20an%20industrially%20low-end%20project%20entailing%20the%20licensed%20manufacture%20of%20assault%20rifles.%20The%20IRRPL%20was%20formed%2C%20amidst%20much%20fanfare%2C%20to%20manufacture%20some%20750%2C000%20AK-203%20rifles%20via%20a%20technology%20transfer%20from%20Russia%2C%20albeit%20with%20a%20high%20level%20of%20indigenisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findias-assault-rifle-induction-woes-continue-with-delays-in-indigenous-ak-203-production%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Assault%20Rifle%20Induction%20Woes%20Continue%20With%20Delays%20in%20Indigenous%20Ak-203%20Production%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Final%20lap%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20military%20officers%2C%20however%2C%20considered%20this%20holdup%20and%20an%20objective%20assessment%20of%20the%20myriad%20hurdles%20Moscow%20faces%20under%20sanctions%2C%20an%20indicator%20that%20the%20halcyon%20period%20of%20bilateral%20military%20commerce%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Moscow%20had%20finally%20run%20its%20course%20and%20was%20fast%20nearing%20an%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20long%20-standing%20commercial%20military%20relationship%20is%20in%20its%20final%20lap%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20retired%20three-star%20Army%20officer%20who%2C%20during%20his%20service%20span%20had%20overseen%20the%20induction%20into%20service%20of%20an%20inordinately%20vast%20amount%20of%20Russian%20materiel.%20And%20though%20this%20association%20will%20%E2%80%98stagger%E2%80%99%20on%2C%20as%20legacy%20Soviet-era%20and%20Russian%20defence%20equipment%20still%20operative%20needed%20technical%20support%2C%20little%20new%2C%20if%20any%20fresh%20buys%2C%20were%20now%20likely%2C%20he%20added%2C%20declining%20to%20be%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%20India%20had%20acquired%20over%20%2420%20billion%20worth%20of%20Russian%20materiel%20which%2C%20along%20with%20kit%20dating%20back%20to%20Soviet%20times%2C%20at%20present%20constituted%20some%2065%25%20of%20platforms%20and%20other%20varied%20equipment%20in%20use%20by%20its%20armed%20forces.%20This%20latter%20phenomenon%20necessitated%20continual%20servicing%2C%20maintenance%2C%20overhaul%2C%20and%20in%20some%20instances%20upgradation%20of%20a%20large%20proportion%20of%20this%20equipment%20by%20their%20Russian%20Original%20Equipment%20Manufacturers.%20But%20ever%20since%20Moscow%20was%20sanctioned%2022%20months%20ago%2C%20this%20facet%20too%20had%20significantly%20dwindled%20following%20enduring%20uncertainty%20over%20the%20continued%20supply%20of%20spares%20and%20components%20to%20sustain%20the%20Indian%20military%E2%80%99s%20serviceable%20Russian%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20easy%20conceding%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20defence%20industrial%20complex%20seems%20to%20concur%2C%20as%20it%20recently%20conceded%20its%20inability%20in%20continuing%20to%20deliver%20military%20kit%20to%20its%20many%20clients%2C%20including%20India%2C%20as%20it%20needed%20to%20prioritise%20%E2%80%98manufacturing%20and%20supplying%20products%20to%20the%20Russian%20Army%E2%80%99.%20In%20an%20October%2019%20press%20statement%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20monopolistic%20joint%20stock%20arms%20export%20company%20Rosonboronexport%20admitted%20to%20facing%20%E2%80%98pressing%20challenges%20faced%20by%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20defence%20industry%20and%20the%20system%20of%20military-technical%20co-operation%E2%80%99.%20Analysts%20interpreted%20these%20%E2%80%98challenges%E2%80%99%20to%20be%20a%20direct%20reference%20to%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20defence%20industry%20supplying%20and%20supporting%20its%20military%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20mis-adventure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20alternative%2C%20Rosonboronexport%20is%20offering%20its%20potential%20foreign%20partners%20%E2%80%98new%20formats%20of%20co-operation%20within%20the%20global%20arms%20market%20trends%E2%80%99%20that%20included%20%E2%80%98technology%20partnerships%E2%80%99%20which%20the%20corporation%20estimated%20would%20double%20to%2040%25%20by%202030.%20Rosonboronexport%20head%20Aleksandr%20Mikheyev%20declared%20that%20his%20conglomerate%20had%20%E2%80%98strong%20competencies%20in%20launching%20licensed%20production%2C%20setting%20up%20joint%20ventures%20and%20conducting%20joint%20research%20and%20development%20with%20foreign%20customers%E2%80%99.%20Such%20an%20arrangement%2C%20the%20press%20release%20added%2C%20provided%20partner%20countries%20the%20opportunity%20to%20%E2%80%98launch%20full-scale%20production%20on%20their%20territory%20and%20develop%20their%20own%20(military)%20industrial%20base%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20press%20note%20provided%20numerous%20such%20examples%20from%20India%2C%20like%20the%20licensed%20production%20and%20maintenance%20of%20Sukhoi%20Su-30%20MKI%20multi-role%20fighters%2C%20T72M%20and%20T90S%20main%20battle%20tanks%2C%20Boyevaya%20Mashina%20Pekhoty%20or%20BMP%201%2F%202%20infantry%20combat%20vehicles%2C%20Ak-203%20assault%20rifles%20and%20assorted%20tank%20and%20other%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F05%2Fsukhoi380.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20IAF%20Su-30%20aircraft.%20Credit%3A%20PIB%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22380%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-139192%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22285%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20IAF%20Su-30%20aircraft.%20Credit%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20deferred%20%C2%A0AK-203%20project%2C%20India%20has%20three%20other%20major%20Russian%20platforms%20on%20order%2C%20all%20of%20which%20were%20plagued%20by%20delays%2C%20and%20possibly%20an%20ambiguous%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20included%20the%20delivery%20of%20two%20of%20five%20Almaz-Antey%20S-400%20Triumf%20self-propelled%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%2C%20acquired%20for%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%20in%20a%20deal%20signed%20in%20October%202018%20for%20%245.5%20billion%2C%20constructing%20two%20Project%201135.6M%20Admiral%20Grigorovich%20guided%20missile%20frigates%20worth%20an%20estimated%20%24950%20million%20at%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Yantar%20Shipyard%20at%20Kaliningrad%20and%20possibly%20leasing%20a%20follow-on%20Project%20971%20%E2%80%98Akula%E2%80%99%20(Schuka-B)-class%20nuclear%20powered%20submarine%20for%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20for%20around%20%243%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202021%20and%20March%202023%20Russia%20had%20delivered%20three%20S-400%20systems%2C%20and%20%C2%A0Rosonboronexport%E2%80%99s%20Mikheyev%20had%20recently%20told%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20state-owned%20news%20agency%20TASS%2C%20that%20the%20remaining%20two%20air%20defence%20systems%20would%20arrive%20by%20end-2023%2C%20which%20has%20not%20happened.%20Military%20officers%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20senior%20Russian%20officials%20continued%20to%20claim%20that%20the%20two%20outstanding%20S-400%20systems%20would%20be%20arriving%20imminently%2C%20but%20they%20simply%20have%20not%2C%20and%20that%20this%20deadline%20remains%20%E2%80%98tenuous%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20defence%20analysts%20claimed%20that%20Russia%20had%20deployed%20several%20S-400%20batteries%20in%20its%20Ukrainian%20%C2%A0campaign%20to%20counter%20the%20US-supplied%20Lockheed%20Martin%20M142%20High%20Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocket%20System%20(HIMARS)%20to%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20military.%20In%20the%20ongoing%20firefight%2C%20some%20S-400%20batteries%20had%20even%20been%20destroyed%20in%20the%20Crimea%20region%2C%20claimed%C2%A0retired%20Brigadier%20Rahul%20Bhonsle%C2%A0of%20the%20Security%20Risks%20consultancy%20Group%20in%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20employment%20of%20S-400%20systems%20by%20Russia%20only%20lessened%C2%A0the%20chances%20of%20India%20receiving%20its%20complement%20of%20two%20missile%20system%20in%20a%20hurry%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Their%20delivery%20schedule%20continues%20to%20remain%C2%A0indeterminate%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlongside%2C%20the%20two%20stealth%20frigates%20that%20were%20scheduled%20for%20delivery%20to%20the%20Navy%20by%20early%202024%20too%20were%20delayed%20by%20at%20least%2012%20months%2C%20if%20not%20more.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurasiantimes.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEurAsian%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ETimes%3C%2Fem%3E%20digital%20news%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20quoting%20an%20unnamed%20officials%2C%20reported%20in%20September%20that%20both%20warships%20had%20been%20launched%20and%20outfitting%20work%20on%20them%20was%20underway%2C%20but%20their%20transfer%20to%20the%20Navy%20had%20been%20deferred%20due%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98focus%20on%20military%20operations%20in%20Ukraine%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20in%20a%20knock-on%20effect%2C%20the%20latter%20project%20that%20included%20building%20two%20similar%20frigates%20under%20a%20separate%20%24500%20million%20contract%2C%20inked%20in%20January%202019%20with%20Goa%20Shipyard%20limited%20(GSL)%20via%20a%20transfer%20of%20technology%2C%20too%20stands%20postponed%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Navy%20faces%20multiple%20challenges%20in%20its%20immediate%20neighbourhood.%20The%20fate%20of%20the%20nuclear-powered%20submarine%20to%20be%20leased%2C%20however%2C%20was%20also%20nebulous%2C%20and%20according%20to%20industry%20sources%2C%20could%20end%20up%20being%20scrapped%20altogether%2C%20further%20weakening%20the%20equipment%20links%20between%20Moscow%20and%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20question%20of%20payment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20complicating%20matters%20was%20the%20enduring%20tussle%20between%20India%20and%20Russia%20in%20evolving%20a%20dependable%20payment%C2%A0structure%2C%20that%20was%20not%20violative%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficial%20sources%20claimed%20that%20over%20%243%20billion%20owed%20to%20Russia%20by%20India%20for%20military%20kit%2C%20spares%20and%20related%20apparatus%20for%20in-service%20equipment%2C%20had%20accumulated%20over%20the%2012-14%20months%2C%20leading%20to%20Moscow%20%E2%80%98pausing%E2%80%99%20all%20further%20credit%20to%20Delhi%20for%20its%20defence%20buy%E2%80%99s.%20The%20rupees%20that%20had%20piled%20up%20under%20the%20mutually%20agreed%20rupee-rouble%20payment%20protocol%20had%20been%20routed%20via%20%E2%80%98vostro%E2%80%99%20accounts%20through%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Sherbank%20and%20VTB%20Bank%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20since%20late%202022%20this%20state%20of%20affairs%20was%20muddled%20further%20by%20massive%20payments%2C%20also%20in%20rupees%2C%20for%20Russian%20oil%20imports%20which%20had%20increased%2050-fold%20after%20the%20Ukraine%20invasion.%20In%20September%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20Sergei%20Lavrov%20had%20reiterated%20that%20Moscow%20faced%20the%20problem%20of%20a%20rupee%20surfeit%20that%20was%20%E2%80%98not%20currently%20useable%E2%80%99.%20He%20told%20reporters%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%20in%20Delhi%20that%20these%20rupees%20needed%20%E2%80%98transferring%E2%80%99%20to%20another%20currency%2C%20and%20that%20an%20alternate%20arrangement%20was%20under%20discussion%20with%20his%20counterpart%20S.%20Jaishankar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20recently%20conceded%20%E2%80%98understandable%20concern%E2%80%99%20over%20the%20trade%20imbalance%20between%20Russia%20and%20India%20for%20defence%20equipment%20and%20told%20reporters%20in%20Delhi%20recently%20that%20the%20two%20countries%20needed%20to%20co-operate%20on%20a%20%E2%80%98very%20urgent%20basis%20%E2%80%99%20to%20address%20this%C2%A0predicament%2C%20but%20did%20not%20elaborate%2C%20nor%20disclose%20any%20roadmap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%20India%20had%20also%20turned%20down%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20to%20settle%20its%20oil%20bills-and%20possibly%2C%20even%20its%20military%20equipment%20outstanding%E2%80%99s-in%20Chinese%20yuan.%20But%20alongside%2C%20it%20had%20seemingly%20also%20not%20finalised%20a%20workable%20solution%20to%20this%20predicament%2C%20as%20Indian%20banks%20continued%20to%20be%20wary%20of%20exploring%20other%20forms%20of%20payments%20to%20Russia%2C%20via%20other%20currencies%2C%20for%20fear%20of%20inviting%20secondary%20sanctions%20from%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%20Earlier%2C%20India%20had%20even%20proposed%20that%20Russia%20utilised%20the%20rupees%20from%20its%20weapon%20sales%20to%20invest%20in%20Indian%20debt%20and%20capital%20markets%2C%20but%20Moscow%20had%20rejected%20the%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20is%20steadily%20undergoing%20a%20makeover%20in%20its%20equipment%20profile%2C%20bringing%20to%20a%20close%20over%20six%20decades%20of%20monopoly%20dominated%20by%20Moscow-supplied%20defence%20goods%20in%20the%20rapidly%20%C2%A0evolving%20global%20strategic%20muddle.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702645604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F03152630%2FFqMbzwUWAAAmT01.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Frussia-ak203-kalashnikov-ukraine-sanction%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20this%20an%20indicator%20that%20the%20halcyon%20period%20of%20bilateral%20military%20commerce%20between%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Moscow%20has%20run%20its%20course%20and%20is%20fast%20nearing%20its%20end%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Frussia-ak203-kalashnikov-ukraine-sanction%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%