ng%20the%20Masala%20Bonds%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMasala%20bonds%20are%20rupee-denominated%20bonds%20issued%20in%20foreign%20markets%2C%20allowing%20Indian%20entities%20to%20raise%20funds%20from%20international%20investors.%20These%20bonds%20are%20an%20instrument%20for%20Indian%20companies%20to%20tap%20into%20global%20capital%20markets%20without%20exposing%20themselves%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20currency%20fluctuations%20since%20the%20issuance%20is%20in%20Indian%20Rupees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20both%20KIIFB%20and%20Isaac%20had%20moved%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20summons%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20in%20relation%20to%20its%20probe%20into%20the%20alleged%20violations%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Exchange%20Management%20Act%20(FEMA)%20in%20the%20issuance%20of%20%E2%80%98Masala%20Bonds%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0petition%C2%A0moved%20by%20Isaac%20challenged%20the%20summons%20issued%20by%20the%20ED%20seeking%20his%20personal%20documents%20as%20well%20as%20those%20of%20his%20family%20members%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20same%20probe%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fmasala-bonds-kerala-high-court-ed-will-withdraw-summons-thomas-isaac-kiifb%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20KIIFB%20challenged%20the%20repeated%20issuance%20of%20summons%20by%20the%20ED%20to%20KIIFB%20officers%2C%20including%20its%20CEO%2C%20K.M.%20Abraham%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20confirmed%20to%20the%20high%20court%20that%20it%20had%20issued%20a%20Non-Objection%20Certificate%20(NOC)%20to%20the%20KIIFB%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Exchange%20Management%20Act%20(FEMA)%20for%20raising%20funds%20through%20masala%20bonds%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20an%20interim%20order%20on%20October%2010%2C%202022%2C%20preventing%20further%20ED%20summons%20for%20two%20months%2C%20Justice%20Ramachandran%20allowed%20the%20ED%20to%20issue%20fresh%20summons%20on%20November%2024.%20This%20decision%20was%20challenged%20by%20Isaac%20and%20KIIFB%20officials%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20stay%20on%20December%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20on%20December%2014%2C%20the%20court%20was%20informed%20of%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20summons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%202022%2C%20Isaac%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fformer-kerala-minister-calls-ed-notice-harassment%5C%22%3Ehad%20termed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20ED%20notice%20to%20him%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98political%20move%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20alleging%20it%20was%20misusing%20all%20investigation%20agencies%20for%20its%20political%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CKIIFB%20is%20the%20primary%20agency%20of%20the%20state%20government%20for%20financing%20large%20and%20critical%20infrastructure%20projects%20and%20had%20last%20year%20raised%20Rs%202%2C150%20crore%20through%20its%20debut%20masala%20bond%20issue%20as%20part%20of%20its%20plan%20to%20mobilise%20Rs%2050%2C000%20crore%20to%20fund%20large%20and%20critical%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20the%20southern%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20Isaac%20had%20written%20on%20his%20Facebook%20page%2C%20reacting%20to%20the%20first%20ED%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702645219000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F08154621%2FKerala-HC.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmasala-bonds-case-ed-summons-to-thomas-isaac-kiifb-officials-withdrawn-kerala-hc-told%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202022%2C%20both%20the%20Kerala%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20Fund%20Board%20and%20Isaac%20had%20moved%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20ED%20summons%20in%20relation%20to%20its%20probe%20into%20the%20alleged%20violations%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Exchange%20Management%20Act%20in%20the%20issuance%20of%20%E2%80%98Masala%20Bonds%E2%80%99.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmasala-bonds-case-ed-summons-to-thomas-isaac-kiifb-officials-withdrawn-kerala-hc-told%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wholesale%20Price-Based%20Inflation%20in%20November%20Was%20Fastest%20in%208%20Months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15180836%2F9015611300_9547bff9f2_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Wholesale%20price-based%20inflation%20rose%20at%20at%200.26%25%20in%20November%202023%2C%20in%20what%20is%20being%20called%20the%20fastest%20pace%20in%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20largely%20thanks%20to%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20the%20price%20of%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWPI%20inflation%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20had%20been%20in%20the%20negative%20zone%20in%20the%20past%20seven%20months%20and%20was%20at%20(-)0.52%25%20in%20October.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPositive%20rate%20of%20inflation%20in%20November%2C%202023%20is%20primarily%20due%20to%20increase%20in%20prices%20of%20food%20articles%2C%20minerals%2C%20machinery%20%26amp%3B%20equipment%2C%20computer%2C%20electronics%20%26amp%3B%20optical%20products%2C%20motor%20vehicles%2C%20other%20transport%20equipment%20and%20other%20manufacturing%20etc%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20the%20commerce%20ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fwholesale-price-inflation-at-0-3-in-november-after-7-months-of-deflation%2Farticleshow%2F106001812.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3ETOI%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20the%20food%20articles%20group%20rose%208.2%25%20in%20November%2C%20faster%20than%20the%201.5%25%20in%20the%20same%20year%20earlier%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVegetable%20prices%2C%20similarly%20rose%2010.4%25%20in%20November%20even%20though%20they%20had%20reduced%2020.1%25%20in%20November%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20reported%20earlier%20that%20retail%20inflation%20%E2%80%93%20measured%20by%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%20%E2%80%93%20rose%205.6%25%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702644330000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15180836%2F9015611300_9547bff9f2_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwholesale-price-based-inflation-in-november-was-fastest-in-8-months%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20has%20said%20that%20this%20rise%20is%20primarily%20due%20to%20increase%20in%20prices%20of%20food%20articles%2C%20minerals%2C%20machinery%20and%20equipment%2C%20computer%2C%20electronics%20and%20optical%20products%2C%20and%20motor%20vehicles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwholesale-price-based-inflation-in-november-was-fastest-in-8-months%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Telangana%20Govt%20Mulls%20Judicial%20Probe%20Into%20Recruitment%20Exam%20Leaks%2C%20Unemployment%20Crisis%20in%20Focus%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15164653%2FGBKRzsKWAAA6EIj.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHyderabad%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Telangana%20chief%20minister%20A.%20Revanth%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20that%20he%20is%20contemplating%20a%20judicial%20inquiry%20into%20the%20leakage%20of%20papers%20for%20government%20recruitment%20exams%20conducted%20by%20the%20Telangana%20State%20Public%20Service%20Commission%20has%20once%20again%20brought%20into%20sharp%20focus%20the%20unemployment%20crisis%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReddy%20said%20he%20will%20shortly%20write%20to%20the%20high%20court%20to%20spare%20a%20sitting%20judge%20to%20oversee%20the%20probe.%20The%20promise%20to%20institute%20a%20judicial%20inquiry%20into%20the%20allegations%20of%20scams%20and%20corruption%20against%20the%20previous%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samiti%20(BRS)%20government%20was%20made%20by%20the%20Congress%20in%20its%20election%20manifesto.%20While%20the%20manifesto%20said%20the%20probe%20would%20be%20taken%20up%20by%20a%20retired%20high%20court%20judge%2C%20Reddy%20went%20a%20step%20further%2C%20seeking%20a%20sitting%20high%20court%20judge%20to%20go%20into%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%E2%80%99s%20functioning%20has%20been%20under%20the%20scanner%2C%20with%20the%20public%20expressing%20outrage%20and%20demanding%20a%20total%20overhaul%20after%20question%20papers%20for%20government%20employment%20were%20repeatedly%20leaked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20change%20of%20guard%2C%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20chairman%20B.%20Janardhan%20Reddy%20submitted%20his%20resignation%20to%20the%20Raj%20Bhavan%20when%20governor%20Tamilisai%20Soundararajan%20was%20away%20in%20Puducherry.%20The%20remaining%20five%20members%20are%20expected%20to%20follow%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20commission%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20resign%20is%20perceived%20as%20an%20attempt%20at%20a%20%E2%80%98safe%20exit%E2%80%99%20amidst%20a%20series%20of%20blunders%20in%20conducting%20recruitment%20exams%20since%20October%20last%20year%2C%20which%20led%20to%20a%20police%20investigation%2C%20protests%20and%20outcry%20from%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resignation%20spree%20has%20given%20the%20new%20chief%20minister%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20premier%20recruitment%20agency%20for%20state%20services.%20But%20the%20panel%20is%20nervous%20about%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20next%20move.%20Soundararajan%20reportedly%20has%20reservations%20about%20accepting%20the%20resignation%20because%20she%20is%20keen%20on%20fixing%20responsibility%20for%20the%20lapses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20rode%20the%20crest%20of%20a%20wave%20of%20anger%20by%20lakhs%20of%20youth%20who%20were%20anxiously%20looking%20for%20job%20notifications%20under%20the%20BRS%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Public%20Service%20Commission%20conducted%20exams%20to%20fill%20up%20vacancies%20for%20groups%20II%2C%20III%20and%20IV%20services%20but%20the%20group%20I%20notification%20for%20higher%20posts%20was%20not%20issued%20for%20several%20years.%20When%20the%20group%20I%20posts%20were%20finally%20notified%20last%20year%2C%20the%20commission%20received%203.8%20lakh%20applications.%20But%20the%20preliminary%20written%20exam%20in%20October%20was%20cancelled%20after%20two%20persons%20working%20for%20the%20commission%20%E2%80%93%20an%20assistant%20section%20officer%20on%20deputation%20and%20an%20outsourced%20software%20professional%20%E2%80%93%20were%20found%20to%20have%20copied%20the%20question%20papers%20on%20a%20pen%20drive%20and%20sold%20it%20to%20candidates%20for%20a%20huge%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BRS%20government%20appointed%20a%20special%20investigation%20team%20headed%20by%20the%20additional%20commissioner%20of%20police%20A.R.%20Srinivas%20to%20conduct%20a%20probe.%20The%20team%20arrested%20108%20accused%20persons%2C%20including%20sellers%20and%20buyers%20of%20question%20papers%2C%20and%20filed%20the%20first%20chargesheet%20in%20court.%20The%20second%20chargesheet%20is%20held%20up%20due%20to%20a%20delay%20in%20receipt%20of%20the%20forensic%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20government%20conducted%20the%20preliminary%20written%20exam%20for%20group%20I%20once%20again%20on%20June%207%20this%20year%20but%20this%20was%20again%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Ftelangana-hc-to-tspsc-hold-group-i-prelims-with-biometrics%2Farticleshow%2F104001109.cms%5C%22%3Ecancelled%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20high%20court%20for%20want%20of%20biometric%20attendance%20of%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20group%20II%20exam%20notification%20was%20issued%20but%20it%20was%20postponed%20as%20the%20question%20paper%20was%20leaked%20in%20some%20other%20exams%20of%20the%20commission.%20The%20notification%20for%20the%20group%20III%20exam%20was%20issued%20but%20the%20date%20was%20not%20fixed%20while%20the%20group%20IV%20preliminary%20exam%20was%20taken%20by%20about%207.5%20lakh%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20all%2C%20the%20commission%20cancelled%2016%20written%20exams%20for%20various%20posts%20in%20four%20categories%20comprising%20the%20groups%2C%20departments%20that%20employed%20assistant%20executive%20engineers%2C%20assistant%20engineers%20with%20diplomas%20and%20divisional%20accounts%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20recruitment%20process%20coming%20to%20a%20standstill%2C%20the%20frustration%20among%20youth%20waiting%20for%20employment%20mounted.%20Many%20of%20them%20come%20from%20rural%20backgrounds%20and%20lived%20in%20rented%20accommodation%20or%20in%20paying%20guest%20hostels%20in%20Hyderabad%20to%20enrol%20in%20coaching%20centres.%20After%20spending%20years%20waiting%20for%20notifications%2C%20they%20returned%20home%20disappointed.%20Their%20struggles%20influenced%20many%20rural%20voters%2C%20who%20felt%20that%20the%20BRS%20government%20was%20indifferent%20to%20the%20plight%20of%20the%20youth.%20The%20death%20by%20suicide%20of%20one%20female%20aspirant%20furthered%20this%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20election%20campaign%2C%20opposition%20parties%2C%20especially%20the%20Congress%2C%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20aspirants.%20The%20Congress%20came%20up%20with%20a%20%E2%80%98youth%20declaration%E2%80%99%20that%20promised%20two%20lakh%20government%20jobs%20within%20one%20year%20of%20forming%20the%20government.%20All%20backlogs%20for%20people%20from%20SC%2C%20ST%2C%20OBC%20and%20minority%20communities%20would%20also%20be%20filled%20within%20a%20year%2C%20the%20party%20said%2C%20alongside%20the%20promise%20to%20release%20a%20%E2%80%98job%20calendar%E2%80%99%20on%20June%202%20every%20year%20to%20display%20vacancies%20in%20all%20departments.%20The%20Congress%20also%20promised%20to%20provide%20an%20allowance%20of%20Rs%204%2C000%20per%20month%20to%20unemployed%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20Congress%20also%20annexed%20a%20job%20calendar%20for%202024%20in%20group%20services%20and%20other%20departments%20in%20its%20election%20manifesto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20counter%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20BRS%20government%20also%20assured%20that%20it%20would%20release%20a%20job%20calendar%20to%20fill%20up%20vacancies%20as%20and%20when%20they%20arose.%20Minister%20K.%20T.%20Rama%20Rao%20met%20the%20hostel%20inmates%20at%20Ashok%20Nagar%20in%20Hyderabad%20where%20a%20clutch%20of%20coaching%20centres%20are%20located%20to%20assure%20them%20of%20immediate%20steps%20to%20revive%20the%20recruitment%20process.%20He%20even%20announced%20that%20he%20would%20meet%20them%20on%20December%204%2C%20the%20day%20after%20the%20declaration%20of%20election%20results%2C%20to%20draw%20up%20the%20calendar.%20But%2C%20the%20party%20lost%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20days%20of%20the%20Congress%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy%20reviewed%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Public%20Service%20Commission%20at%20an%20official%20meeting.%20It%20was%20on%20the%20same%20day%20that%20the%20chairman%20and%20members%20of%20the%20commission%20made%20public%20their%20desire%20to%20quit%2C%20apparently%20to%20facilitate%20the%20reorganisation%20of%20the%20commission%20and%20take%20steps%20against%20the%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20member%20Karem%20Ravinder%20Reddy%20said%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20on%20them%20for%20the%20past%20eight%20months%20though%20they%20did%20no%20wrong.%20This%20is%20why%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20members%20decided%20to%20quit.%20Another%20member%2C%20A.%20Satyanarayana%2C%20released%20a%20letter%20to%20youth%20saying%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20members%20spent%20sleepless%20nights%20after%20the%20question%20papers%20were%20leaked.%20Some%20vested%20interests%20wanted%20the%20abolition%20of%20the%20commission%20while%20some%20demanded%20the%20removal%20of%20individuals%2C%20he%20claimed.%20It%20was%20untenable%20for%20them%20to%20continue%20due%20to%20their%20mental%20agony%20and%20anguish%2C%20Satyanarayana%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20commission%2C%20with%20a%20chairman%20and%20seven%20members%2C%20was%20constituted%20on%20May%2021%2C%202021.%20Two%20members%20retired%20after%20attaining%20the%20age%20of%20retirement%20(62%20years).%20In%20all%2C%20four%20member%20posts%20were%20vacant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhanta%20Chakrapani%2C%20a%20former%20chairman%2C%20said%20the%20abolition%20of%20the%20commission%20was%20not%20a%20good%20idea.%20The%20Congress%20government%20should%20instead%20fill%20up%20four%20vacancies%20and%20appoint%20one%20of%20them%20as%20the%20in-charge%20chairman%2C%20he%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702643402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15164653%2FGBKRzsKWAAA6EIj.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftelangana-judicial-probe-recruitment-exam-leaks-unemployment-crisis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20all%2C%20the%20Telangana%20State%20Public%20Service%20Commission%20cancelled%2016%20written%20exams%20for%20various%20posts%20in%20four%20categories%20because%20of%20various%20reasons%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0including%20leakage%20of%20papers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftelangana-judicial-probe-recruitment-exam-leaks-unemployment-crisis%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22COP28%20Agreement%20Suggests%20the%20Days%20of%20Fossil%20Fuels%20Are%20Numbered%2C%20but%20Climate%20Crisis%20Is%20Not%20Yet%26nbsp%3BAverted%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20negotiators%20stagger%20towards%20their%20beds%20in%20Dubai%20and%20another%20year%E2%80%99s%20climate%20talks%20come%20to%20a%20close%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20take%20stock.%20Did%20COP28%20achieve%20the%20big%20breakthrough%20the%20world%20needs%20on%20climate%20change%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProbably%20not.%20But%20the%20final%20agreement%20%E2%80%93%20met%20with%20an%20ovation%20%E2%80%93%20includes%20a%20first%20call%20for%20nations%20to%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20step%20short%20of%20a%20commitment%20to%20phasing%20the%20fuels%20out%2C%20as%20some%20delegates%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F13%2Fcop28-landmark-deal-agreed-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3Epushed%20for%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20development%20suggests%20the%20days%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20are%20numbered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overriding%20question%20the%20world%20now%20faces%20is%20whether%20the%20broad%20commitments%20nations%20agreed%20to%20are%20enough%20as%20climate%20change%20gathers%20pace.%20The%20answer%2C%20alarmingly%2C%20is%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUAE%3A%20controversial%20hosts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%E2%80%99s%20talks%20were%20controversial%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20oil%20man%20Sultan%20Al%20Jaber%20as%20COP28%20president%20fuelled%20concerns%20about%20the%20hosting%20role%20of%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20%E2%80%93%20a%20country%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcop28-inside-the-united-arab-emirates-the-oil-giant-hosting-2023-climate-change-summit-217859%5C%22%3Esignificant%20interests%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20sustaining%20a%20fossil%20fuel%20economy.%20Then%20came%20reports%20Al%20Jaber%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F03%2Fback-into-caves-cop28-president-dismisses-phase-out-of-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3Ehad%20questioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20scientific%20rationale%20for%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change%2C%20amid%20reports%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20trade%20negotiations%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fscience-environment-67508331%5C%22%3Esidelines%20of%20negotiations%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20this%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fscience-environment-67607289%5C%22%3Eunprecedented%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20lobbyists%20and%20geoengineering%20advocates%20attended%20the%20talks.%20This%20did%20not%20create%20the%20ideal%20conditions%20for%20action%20on%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Loss%20and%20damane%E2%80%99%20breakthrough%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20their%20credit%2C%20the%20organisers%20had%20an%20early%20win%20with%20an%20agreement%20to%20establish%20a%20%E2%80%9Closs%20and%20damage%E2%80%9D%20fund%20whereby%20richer%20nations%20compensate%20poorer%20nations%20for%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%20The%20creation%20of%20this%20fund%20is%20one%20of%20the%20big%20outcomes%20of%20the%20talks.%20It%E2%80%99s%20taken%20a%20long%20time%20to%20get%20here%2C%20after%20initially%20being%20suggested%20by%20Vanuatu%20in%201991%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcop27-one-big-breakthrough-but-ultimately-an-inadequate-response-to-the-climate-crisis-194056%5C%22%3Esupported%20in%20principle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20talks%20in%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20it%20needed%3F%20Because%20developing%20states%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20damage%20done%20by%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20have%20limited%20ability%20to%20meet%20the%20cost%20of%20repair%20and%20rebuilding.%20The%20fund%20also%20points%20to%20the%20particular%20obligations%20of%20developed%20states%20and%20significant%20emitters%20who%20have%20largely%20caused%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20still%20big%20questions%20about%20the%20measure%20%E2%80%93%20most%20importantly%2C%20how%20well%20it%20will%20be%20funded.%20Despite%20the%20fanfare%2C%20just%20US%24700%20million%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F06%2F700m-pledged-to-loss-and-damage-fund-cop28-covers-less-than-02-percent-needed%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20committed%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20far%20to%20the%20fund%20aimed%20at%20compensating%20states%20for%20damage%20that%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets-global.website-files.com%2F605869242b205050a0579e87%2F655b50e163c953059360564d_L%2526DC_L%2526D_Package_for_COP28_20112023_1227.pdf%5C%22%3Erecent%20estimates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20already%20runs%20into%20the%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20concerns%20over%20having%20the%20fund%20administrated%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fnov%2F29%2Fwhy-loss-and-damage-funds-are-key-to-climate-justice-for-developing-countries-at-cop28%5C%22%3Equestionable%3C%2Fa%3E%20environmental%20credentials%20and%20a%20patchy%20record%20on%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20fund%20itself%20is%20an%20admission%20of%20failure.%20It%E2%80%99s%20needed%20only%20because%20the%20international%20community%20has%20failed%20to%20stop%20climate%20change%20from%20happening%2C%20and%20is%20unlikely%20to%20prevent%20it%20reaching%20dangerous%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeckchairs%20on%20the%20Titanic%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20talks%20went%20on%2C%20they%20got%20harder.%20The%20tricky%20topic%3A%20fossil%20fuels.%20It%20may%20amaze%20outsiders%2C%20but%20this%2C%20the%2028th%20annual%20climate%20talks%2C%20is%20the%20first%20time%20nations%20have%20directly%20addressed%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels.%20Last%20year%2C%20nations%20agreed%20to%20accelerate%20the%20exit%20from%20coal%20%E2%80%93%20the%20dirtiest%20fuel%20%E2%80%93%20but%20said%20nothing%20of%20gas%20or%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20days%2C%20debate%20raged%20over%20whether%20to%20apply%20phrases%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cphasing%20out%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cphasing%20down%E2%80%9D%20or%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cunabated%E2%80%9D%20to%20fossil%20fuels.%20Even%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Ccould%E2%80%9D%20became%20controversial%2C%20when%20tied%20to%20the%20suggestion%20countries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fsustainability%2Fclimate-energy%2Fcop28-presidency-wants-historic-mention-fossil-fuels-text-up-nations-2023-12-12%5C%22%3Emight%20consider%3C%2Fa%3E%20limiting%20fossil%20fuel%20production%20and%20consumption.%20To%20victims%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20the%20arguments%20might%20look%20like%20rearranging%20deckchairs%20on%20the%20Titanic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20nations%20were%20prepared%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20need%20to%20eliminate%20fossil%20fuels.%20Others%20noted%20the%20need%20for%20a%20future%20transition%20without%20compromising%20their%20need%20to%20develop%20or%20earn%20export%20income.%20Still%20others%20suggested%20the%20effects%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20might%20be%20minimised%20through%20technologies%20such%20as%20carbon%20capture%20and%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20198%20participating%20countries%20needed%20to%20approve%20any%20final%20declaration.%20So%20you%20can%20see%20the%20difficulty%20in%20reaching%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20100%20countries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F12%2F12%2Fclimate%2Fcop28-climate-summit-agreement-tuesday%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Ehave%20pushed%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20global%20commitment%20to%20a%20total%20phase-out%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20But%20nations%20that%20profit%20immensely%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20Russia%2C%20Iran%2C%20Iraq%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2Flive%2F2023%2Fdec%2F11%2Fcop28-live-time-to-be-ambitious-says-president-as-summit-enters-final-days%5C%22%3Eopposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20any%20mention%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20the%20final%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20draft%20of%20the%20declaration%20did%20not%20go%20down%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHost%20negotiators%20attempted%20to%20broker%20a%20deal%20between%20the%20competing%20interests%20by%20omitting%20any%20reference%20to%20phasing%20%E2%80%9Cout%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cdown%E2%80%9D.%20Instead%2C%20they%20suggested%20countries%20%E2%80%9Ccould%E2%80%9D%20consider%20reducing%20production%20and%20consumption%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20The%20compromise%20text%20produced%20by%20COP28%20president%20Al%20Jaber%20and%20his%20team%20seemed%20to%20err%20on%20the%20side%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20interests.%20Despite%20this%2C%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20backers%20were%20still%20opposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutcry%20was%20swift%20from%20advocates%20for%20strong%20climate%20action.%20The%20draft%20was%20labelled%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeath%20certificate%E2%80%9D%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F12%2Fcop-28-australia-us-and-uk-say-they-wont-sign-agreement-that-would-be-death-certificate-for-small-islands%5C%22%3Evulnerable%20small%20island%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20a%20%3Ca%3Ewithering%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20from%20concerned%20states%2C%20NGOs%20and%20even%20states%20with%20patchier%20climate%20records%20such%20as%20Australia%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Canada%20and%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20agreement%20%E2%80%93%20but%20is%20it%20enough%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20talks%20extended%20well%20beyond%20the%20original%20deadline%2C%20it%20came%20as%20some%20surprise%20that%20the%20final%20document%20was%20endorsed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Flive%2Fworld-67674841%5C%22%3Erelatively%20swiftly%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20version%20was%20more%20strident%20on%20the%20contribution%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20some%20advocates%20saw%20this%20as%20a%20significant%20signal.%20It%20asserted%20that%20the%20transition%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20needed%20to%20take%20place%20quickly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F13%2Fcop28-landmark-deal-agreed-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3Ethough%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%20manner%2C%20accelerating%20action%20in%20this%20critical%20decade%2C%20so%20as%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20by%202050%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20says%20something%20about%20the%20glacial%20pace%20of%20climate%20talks%20since%20they%20began%20in%201992%20that%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20contribution%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20climate%20change%20has%20ever%20been%20acknowledged%20in%20a%20final%20COP%20document.%20And%20here%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F12%2Fwhy-implementation-matters-in-the-global-fight-again-the-climate-crisis%5C%22%3Ecritics%20lamented%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20lack%20of%20detail%20over%20how%20goals%20would%20be%20implemented%20or%20commitments%20realised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conference%20also%20delivered%20important%20commitments%20to%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%2C%20expanding%20nuclear%20power%2C%20and%20a%20new%20pledge%20to%20cut%20emissions%20from%20cooling%20technologies%20such%20as%20air%20conditioning%2C%20which%20will%20become%20increasingly%20important%20as%20the%20world%20heats%20up.%20The%20talks%20also%20saw%20recognition%20of%20the%20increasingly%20significant%20role%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cop28.com%2Fen%2Ffood-and-agriculture%5C%22%3Eagricultural%20sector%20in%20contributing%20to%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20must%20be%20done.%20In%202023%2C%20temperatures%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe360.yale.edu%2Fdigest%2F1.5-degrees-scientific-consensus%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DOn%2520a%2520monthly%2520scale%252C%2520it%2Cexpected%2520to%2520surpass%25201.5%2520degrees.%5C%22%3Espiking%20past%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20crucial%20threshold%20of%201.5%C2%B0C.%20The%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Funs-global-stocktake-on-climate-offers-a-sobering-emissions-reckoning-but-there-are-also-signs-of-progress-217093%5C%22%3Estocktake%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20emissions%20cuts%20released%20in%20advance%20of%20the%20talks%20shows%20our%20current%20efforts%20are%20not%20enough%20to%20stop%20further%20warming.%20Countries%20such%20as%20Australia%20advocated%20stronger%20language%20on%20ending%20fossil%20fuels%20while%20maintaining%20a%20steady%20pipeline%20of%20new%20fossil%20fuel%20projects%20at%20home.%20It%E2%80%99s%20little%20wonder%2C%20then%2C%20that%20the%20lead%20negotiator%20of%20the%20the%20Alliance%20of%20Small%20Island%20States%20said%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F13%2Fcop28-landmark-deal-agreed-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3Ethe%20process%20has%20failed%20us%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20and%20despite%20the%20diplomatic%20achievement%20of%20an%20agreement%20that%20looked%20unlikely%20only%20hours%20earlier%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20hard%20to%20say%20the%20international%20community%20is%20taking%20this%20enormous%20challenge%20as%20seriously%20as%20it%20should.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F219597%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconver